MasterVariable.Description: Encryption type used when pre-provisioning Bitlocker. The EY standard is FULL

MasterVariable.Name: EY-BDE-ENCRYPTION-METHOD
MasterVariable.Description: Encryption method used when pre-provisioning Bitlocker. The EY standard is XTSAES256

MasterVariable.Name: EY-BDE-PREPROVISION-PHASE
MasterVariable.Description: Is used to control at which stage the disk will start to be Bitlocker encrypted (pre-provisioned). Possible values are 'WINPE', 'FULLOS'. If the variable is not set or if it contains any other value (e.g. 'SKIP', then the disk encryption will not be started by the "EY - Pre-Provision Bitlocker" step

MasterVariable.Name: EY-BDE-TPMALLOWEDSTATES-HARDLINK
MasterVariable.Description: Pipe seperated list of allowed TPM states that is checked before starting a Bitlocker Hardlink. Setting this to 2.0 only would prevent a 1.2 PC from being able to kick off a Bitlocker Hardlink. If this variable is not set, a Bitlocker Hardlink will not be possible. Examples of valid values are: 1.2 - 1.2 | 2.0 NOTPM | 1.2 | 2.0

MasterVariable.Name: EY-BDE-TPMALLOWEDSTATES-NEWBDEINSTALL
MasterVariable.Description: Pipe seperated list of allowed TPM states that is checked before starting a Bitlocker Build (including Refresh/Replace). If this variable is not set, a Bitlocker Build will not be possible. For Hardlink, the variable EY-BDETPMALLOWEDSTATES-HARDLINK is used instead.Examples of valid values are: 1.2 - 1.2 | 2.0 - NOTPM | 1.2 | 2.0

Variable.Name: EY-BDE-ENCRYPTION-FLAGS
Variable.Description: Encryption type used when pre-provisioning Bitlocker. The EY standard is FULL

Variable.Name: EY-BDE-ENCRYPTION-METHOD
Variable.Description: Encryption method used when pre-provisioning Bitlocker. The EY standard is XTSAES256

Variable.Name: EY-BDE-PREPROVISION-PHASE
Variable.Description: Is used to control at which stage the disk will start to be Bitlocker encrypted (pre-provisioned). Possible values are 'WINPE', 'FULLOS'. If the variable is not set or if it contains any other value (e.g. 'SKIP', then the disk encryption will not be started by the "EY - Pre-Provision Bitlocker" step

Variable.Name: EY-BDE-TPMALLOWEDSTATES-NEWBDEINSTALL
Variable.Description: Pipe seperated list of allowed TPM states that is checked before starting a Bitlocker Build (including Refresh/Replace). If this variable is not set, a Bitlocker Build will not be possible. For Hardlink, the variable EY-BDETPMALLOWEDSTATES-HARDLINK is used instead.Examples of valid values are: 1.2 - 1.2 | 2.0 - NOTPM | 1.2 | 2.0

Variable.Name: EY-BTS-COPY-PACKAGES-LO-LEVEL1
Variable.Description: Packages to copy for this level. Delimit using §.

Variable.Name: EY-BTS-COPY-PACKAGES-PERM-LO-LEVEL1
Variable.Description: Permanent packages to copy for this level. These packages won't be cleaned up by any of our tools.
